<title>USA: Fruit of the Loom cutting 800 jobs.</title>
<headline>Fruit of the Loom cutting 800 jobs.</headline>
<dateline>CHICAGO 1996-10-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Fruit of the Loom Inc said it is reducing the workforce at two of its Kentucky plants by a total of 800 jobs.</p>
<p>It is eliminating 400 of 2,100 positions in Jamestown, Ky. and 400 of 3,300 in Campbellsville, Ky.</p>
<p>The apparel maker said global competitive pressures were behind the cuts.  </p>
<p>Fruit of the Loom spokesman Mark Steinkrauss said the company does not expect to incur any charges related to the layoffs.</p>
<p>Steinkrauss said employees were given a 60-day notice.</p>
<p>The action, he said, was taken to balance the company's inventories, and &quot;We need to continue to work on that issue.&quot;</p>
<p>	   -- Chicago newsdesk 312 408-8787</p>
